      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BE A COWBOY (4) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by a neck at this track in a handy 19.77. Awkwardly drawn but has the ability and in winning form. Can measure up again. BLAME ESMERALDA (2) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (19.65) at this track behind Fire Up Mark in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Can feature again. JAZZ HANDS (8) stuck on well last time to finish 1.75 lengths back in third (19.89) at this track in a Bottom Up - Grade 5 over 350m. Will give a great sight again. ASTON RECORD (1) can feature with the right run.",
